        <div id="home">
          <div class="grid_17 omega articleTitle">Social Return on Investment (SROI) Analysis Online Training<hr /></div>
          <div class="grid_17 omega text_content">
            <p>This self-paced online training is designed for individuals and organizations who wish to learn about <b>Social Return on Investment (SROI) Analysis</b> and how it can be used to <b>measure, communicate</b>, and <b>improve</b> the <b>impacts</b> of their work.  SROI Analysis is a <b>participatory process</b> for understanding, measuring, and reporting on the<b> social, environmental</b>, and <b>economic value</b> generated by an <b>organization, program</b>, or <b>policy</b>.  As an innovative management and investment tool, SROI Analysis can guide how to allocate valuable resources and improve performance in order to achieve <b>greater social impacts</b>.</p>
          <p>The SROI Analysis framework can be used by <u>various types</u> of <u>organizations</u> including:</p>
          <p><ul>
          <li>non-profit, community-based, and non-government organizations (NGOs),</li> 
          <li>for-profit social ventures and corporate social responsibility programs,</li> 
          <li>foundations, social investors, and private donors,</li> 
          <li>government agencies, etc.</li> 
          </ul></p>
          <p>It can be used to guide:</p>
          <p><ul>
            <li>strategic planning,</li>
            <li>attracting investment and making investment decisions,</li>
            <li>managing and improving relationships with key stakeholders (including target beneficiaries),</li>
            <li>program implementation, program (or organization) evaluation, performance improvement,</li>
            <li>organization accountability, informed decision-making, change management/leadership, etc.</li>
          </ul></p>
          <p></p>
          <p>Designed by <a href="#aboutShubhaKumar" class="navaboutShubhaKumar">Shubha Kumar, MPH, PhD(c)</a>, this online training presents an introduction to SROI Analysis, including how to carry it out, along with various examples applied in the global health and development context. The training is based upon the latest version of SROI Analysis as outlined in <a href="http://www.thesroinetwork.org/component/option,com_docman/task,cat_view/gid,29/Itemid,38/" target="blank"><i>A Guide to Social Return on Investment Analysis</i></a> (by Nicholls, Lawlor, Neitzert, and Godspeed (UK Office of the Third Sector, 2009)) and should take approximately 90 minutes to complete.</p>
          <p><strong>To access the training or its demo version, you will need to login using your username and password information.  To request a login for either of these, please email Shubha Kumar at <a href="mailto:skumar@globalsroi.com">skumar@globalsroi.com</a></strong></p>
