          <div class="grid_17 omega text_content">
            <p>Shubha Kumar is currently a PhD Candidate at the University of California Los Angeles (UCLA) working on her dissertation on Social Return on Investment Analysis (estimated completion in 2011).  She earned her Bachelors of Science in Biology and Masters in Public Health (emphasis in Management and Policy) at UCLA.  Prior to her doctorate studies, she served as the Chief Operating Officer of an international humanitarian NGO.  She has been a consultant to various private and public organizations, as well as a teaching associate at UCLA and guest lecturer on other university campuses for courses on healthcare management, leadership, change management, and international development.  She has travelled throughout Africa, Asia, Europe, the Middle East, South America, and the Caribbean.</p>
            <p>She has given presentations on SROI Analysis, both domestically and internationally at various conferences attended by academics and practitioners, and is currently in the process of submitting articles to relevant journals in this area.</p>
            <p>To watch a recent video of Shubha Kumar speaking on SROI Analysis at the Global Health Metrics and Evaluation Conference (March 16th, 2011, in Seattle, USA), please click <a href="http://ghme.org/new-quantitative-tools-priority-setting" target="blank"><b>here</b></a>.</p>
            <p><b>To contact Shubha Kumar, please send her an email at <a href="mailto:skumar@globalsroi.com">skumar@globalsroi.com</a>.</b></p>
